  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Store Operations Intern",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a Store Operations Intern to support the Store Executive in performing daily store, warehouse, and inventory management activities in compliance with the organisation’s ISO 9001 Quality Management System (QMS). </p><h3>Responsibilities </h3><ul><li><p>Assist in receiving incoming goods and verifying against shipping documents and purchase orders. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Support preparation of Goods Receiving Notes (GRN). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Assist in tracking stock movement and updating relevant records for traceability. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Help conduct monthly stock checks and preparation of inventory reports. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Support proper storage of goods according to QMS requirements. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Assist in packing goods for delivery following packaging standards. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Maintain cleanliness and 7S housekeeping within the storage area. </p></li></ul><p><ul><li>Support preparation of documentation for QMS reporting. <br /></li><li>Ensure all forms, records, and checklists related to inventory and goods receipt are completed accurately and filed in accordance with QMS documentation control procedures. </li></ul></p><ul><li><p>Perform additional operational duties as assigned. </p></li></ul><p></p><h3>Competency Requirements </h3><ul><li><p>Basic knowledge of warehouse or inventory operations (preferred). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ability to follow ISO 9001 documented procedures. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Attention to detail in documentation and stock recording. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Proficiency in Microsoft Office. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Good communication skills and willingness to learn. </p></li></ul><p><ul><li>Physically able to handle light to moderate lifting.</li></ul></p>",
